1
00:01:31,840 --> 00:01:32,319
Bro.

2
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:40,719
Bro, what are you...

3
00:01:44,879 --> 00:01:45,560
Golden Guard Pan.

4
00:01:52,959 --> 00:01:53,640
Pan Yucheng.

5
00:01:54,159 --> 00:01:55,519
Looks like there's no escaping today.

6
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:57,959
Bring on whatever tricks you've got.

7
00:01:58,400 --> 00:02:00,120
If I so much as flinch today,

8
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:01,719
I'm not your daddy.

9
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:04,159
But you listen to me carefully.

10
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:06,680
Man acts, and Heaven watches.

11
00:02:08,159 --> 00:02:09,719
Every torture you use on me today,

12
00:02:10,159 --> 00:02:11,080
sooner or later,

13
00:02:11,599 --> 00:02:13,039
will come back on you.

14
00:02:16,319 --> 00:02:17,800
You're tough, huh?

15
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:38,960
Five taels.

16
00:02:42,039 --> 00:02:42,759
I get a share too.

17
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:43,960
Why would I give it to you?

18
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:45,280
Because I bet too.

19
00:02:45,639 --> 00:02:46,199
When did you ever bet?

20
00:02:46,319 --> 00:02:47,280
You weren't even part of our chat.

21
00:02:47,439 --> 00:02:48,280
I said it in my head.

22
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:50,039
If you disagree, I'll beat the piss out of him,

23
00:02:50,199 --> 00:02:51,039
and you still lose.

24
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:51,639
Th-this...

25
00:02:51,759 --> 00:02:52,840
I heard your inner voice.

26
00:02:53,479 --> 00:02:53,960
Five taels.

27
00:02:58,439 --> 00:03:00,120
Are you guys even human?

28
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:01,879
In the middle of the night,

29
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:04,039
playing "Lights Out" with me here?

30
00:03:05,039 --> 00:03:06,280
Wait, are YOU even human?

31
00:03:07,039 --> 00:03:08,120
The boys have been at it all day,

32
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:09,680
finally got those corrupt officials sorted out,

33
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:11,039
and you say we're not human?

34
00:03:11,680 --> 00:03:12,479
Exactly.

35
00:03:12,879 --> 00:03:14,120
We played deaf and dumb for you.

36
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:15,360
You think it's easy on us?

37
00:03:15,879 --> 00:03:16,759
These men here,

38
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:18,039
their crimes are countless.

39
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:19,599
Too many to even write down.

40
00:03:19,759 --> 00:03:20,840
Especially the Imperial Uncle.

41
00:03:21,319 --> 00:03:22,199
The crimes he committed,

42
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:23,759
warrant a hundred deaths.

43
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:25,439
Based on all this,

44
00:03:25,879 --> 00:03:26,599
I figure

45
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:28,520
you've got a shot at surviving.

46
00:03:29,199 --> 00:03:30,080
As for what we can do,

47
00:03:30,680 --> 00:03:31,400
that's all of it.

48
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:33,199
Someone will come soon,

49
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:34,479
to take you to face the Emperor.

50
00:03:35,439 --> 00:03:36,199
Once you're at the palace,

51
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:38,080
you must fight for yourself,

52
00:03:38,599 --> 00:03:39,840
for the best chance to survive.

53
00:03:40,759 --> 00:03:42,199
Seems I misjudged old Pan.

54
00:03:42,879 --> 00:03:43,960
He's actually a decent man.

55
00:03:46,080 --> 00:03:47,080
You...

56
00:03:48,319 --> 00:03:49,080
What "you"?

57
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:51,840
Alright, stop standing around.

58
00:03:52,319 --> 00:03:53,000
Take him out.

59
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:00,120
Careful.

60
00:04:39,199 --> 00:04:40,680
Not bad, Chen.

61
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:41,720
You kidding?

62
00:04:42,439 --> 00:04:43,279
I'm a soldier.

63
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:44,759
Some soldier.

64
00:04:50,439 --> 00:04:51,879
Who has the absolute nerve,

65
00:04:52,279 --> 00:04:53,720
daring to break into our Inspectorate?

66
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:55,639
Investigate.

67
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:57,680
No matter who's behind this,

68
00:04:57,839 --> 00:04:58,720
drag them out for me.

69
00:04:59,160 --> 00:04:59,639
Yes, sir.

70
00:05:00,279 --> 00:05:01,000
Golden Guard Pan.

71
00:05:01,959 --> 00:05:02,839
Are you sure you want to investigate?

72
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:04,560
Investigate.

73
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:06,040
The Empress and the Third Prince

74
00:05:06,399 --> 00:05:07,600
both want vengeance for the Imperial Uncle.

75
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:09,279
Next is the Left Chancellor.

76
00:05:10,399 --> 00:05:11,439
And I killed the Imperial Uncle,

77
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:13,319
a crime punishable by clan extermination.

78
00:05:14,639 --> 00:05:16,759
The Ning family is wed to the Chancellor.

79
00:05:17,439 --> 00:05:19,920
This may drag in the Chancellor's household.

80
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:22,800
This is the Imperial City.

81
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:24,560
At the Emperor's very feet.

82
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:27,000
If I die at the Inspectorate today,

83
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:29,800
His Majesty will surely fly into a rage.

84
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:31,519
Then he'll pour all his focus

85
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:32,759
into hunting down the killer.

86
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:33,639
That way,

87
00:05:34,279 --> 00:05:35,680
they'll have a chance to escape blame.

88
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:46,879
Am I wrong about this?

89
00:05:49,399 --> 00:05:50,040
Ning.

90
00:05:50,519 --> 00:05:51,399
Haven't you noticed

91
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,839
you have a real talent for stirring up trouble?

92
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:55,240
Brother,

93
00:05:55,879 --> 00:05:57,199
even though you're extraordinarily gifted,

94
00:05:57,600 --> 00:05:58,240
just look around.

95
00:05:58,360 --> 00:05:59,319
Every single person who wants you dead

96
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:00,639
is some kind of major figure.

97
00:06:01,439 --> 00:06:02,720
Doesn't matter.

98
00:06:03,319 --> 00:06:04,759
If I'm willing to face death,

99
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:07,519
I'd dare to drag Emperor Xuan off his throne.

100
00:06:07,639 --> 00:06:08,480
Just shut up already.

101
00:06:08,959 --> 00:06:09,759
If you don't want to live,

102
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:10,879
don't drag your brothers down with you.

103
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:11,560
Exactly.

104
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:15,240
Dawn is almost here.

105
00:06:15,759 --> 00:06:16,839
Hurry to the palace for the audience.

106
00:06:17,519 --> 00:06:18,000
Let's go.

107
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:39,560
Who knew the one who dared behead the

108
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:42,480
Imperial Uncle was such a young lad.

109
00:06:45,600 --> 00:06:48,399
So Uncle Tianxuan really is Emperor Xuan.

110
00:06:57,959 --> 00:06:59,040
How dare you, Ning Chen!

111
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:01,519
In the presence of His Majesty,

112
00:07:02,319 --> 00:07:04,600
why haven't you bowed yet?

113
00:07:15,839 --> 00:07:17,639
Greetings, Your Majesty.

114
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:29,639
Your Majesty.

115
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:31,319
I have a matter to report.

116
00:07:31,759 --> 00:07:33,480
The Inspectorate was attacked last night.

117
00:07:33,759 --> 00:07:35,000
The intruders had a clear target.

118
00:07:35,279 --> 00:07:36,079
It was Ning Chen.

119
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:37,759
How audacious!

120
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:39,800
They dared strike at the Inspectorate?

121
00:07:40,279 --> 00:07:42,360
Do they have any regard for Us at all?

122
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:44,639
Please quell your anger, Your Majesty.

123
00:07:45,199 --> 00:07:46,360
We have failed in our duties.

124
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:48,959
Is that all you ever say?

125
00:07:49,279 --> 00:07:49,720
Geng Jing.

126
00:07:50,160 --> 00:07:50,759
Investigate this.

127
00:07:50,959 --> 00:07:51,959
Get to the bottom of it.

128
00:07:52,160 --> 00:07:53,279
We do not care who they are.

129
00:07:53,439 --> 00:07:55,000
We shall execute their entire clan.

130
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:57,120
I obey Your decree.

131
00:08:05,399 --> 00:08:06,000
Your Majesty.

132
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:08,279
Ning Chen has not yet been tried.

133
00:08:12,079 --> 00:08:12,720
Very well.

134
00:08:13,279 --> 00:08:15,480
Let the court speak, then.

135
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:19,079
How should Ning Chen be punished?

136
00:08:19,519 --> 00:08:20,519
Punished?

137
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:22,519
Will Your Majesty not execute Ning Chen?

138
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:25,000
Sire, Ning Chen defied the law,

139
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:25,879
slaughtered the innocent,

140
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:27,000
and scorned imperial authority.

141
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:29,879
Any of these warrants clan execution.

142
00:08:30,759 --> 00:08:31,920
I humbly petition:

143
00:08:32,159 --> 00:08:34,360
drag Ning Chen out and behead him at once,

144
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:35,440
to make an example of him.

145
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:41,360
Since the court all deems Ning Chen worthy of death,

146
00:08:41,759 --> 00:08:43,519
fine, drag him out and behead him.

147
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:47,559
Your Majesty is wise.

148
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:51,360
Uncle Tianxuan.

149
00:08:51,679 --> 00:08:52,679
You're not even going to try me?

150
00:08:53,639 --> 00:08:54,600
That's awfully hasty, isn't it?

151
00:08:55,919 --> 00:08:56,559
Your Majesty.

152
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:59,399
Ning Chen has indeed committed grave crimes,

153
00:08:59,559 --> 00:09:01,159
but when he set out for Chongzhou,

154
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:02,559
You bestowed upon him the imperial sword,

155
00:09:02,759 --> 00:09:06,080
granting him the right to execute before reporting.

156
00:09:10,159 --> 00:09:11,840
When did His Majesty give me an imperial sword?

157
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:16,799
Your Majesty.

158
00:09:17,159 --> 00:09:18,720
The imperial uncle, as royalty,

159
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:20,840
should have loved the people as his own children,

160
00:09:21,159 --> 00:09:21,960
and cared for them.

161
00:09:22,559 --> 00:09:24,240
Yet he treated lives as worthless,

162
00:09:24,399 --> 00:09:25,559
abducted innocent women,

163
00:09:26,159 --> 00:09:28,600
and made life unbearable in Chongzhou.

164
00:09:28,879 --> 00:09:32,000
Ning Chen had no choice but to slay him.

165
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:34,720
Had Ning Chen turned a blind eye,

166
00:09:34,919 --> 00:09:37,200
he would have failed Heaven's grace above,

167
00:09:37,519 --> 00:09:39,200
and the common folk below.

168
00:09:39,639 --> 00:09:41,840
He is young and lacked foresight.

169
00:09:42,639 --> 00:09:43,799
Driven by hot blood,

170
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:48,320
he made the rash move to slay the Uncle.

171
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:49,440
This old servant believes

172
00:09:49,799 --> 00:09:51,039
there were grounds for his deed,

173
00:09:51,559 --> 00:09:52,879
and the crime does not warrant death.

174
00:09:56,960 --> 00:09:57,799
What's going on?

175
00:09:58,799 --> 00:10:00,279
What kind of act are you two putting on?

176
00:10:02,679 --> 00:10:04,159
We did grant him the imperial sword,

177
00:10:04,519 --> 00:10:07,440
but not to slay royal kin at will.

178
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:08,480
Your Majesty.

179
00:10:08,879 --> 00:10:10,639
Though the uncle was royal kin,

180
00:10:10,919 --> 00:10:12,399
he was also a corrupt official.

181
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:14,159
Ning Chen's slaying of him

182
00:10:14,399 --> 00:10:17,480
hardly amounts to scorning imperial might.

183
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:20,799
Something's off here.

184
00:10:24,240 --> 00:10:24,919
Your Majesty,

185
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:27,399
Ning Chen is but a lowly Silver Guard.

186
00:10:27,679 --> 00:10:30,320
Why grant him the imperial sword?

187
00:10:33,759 --> 00:10:36,279
Because We deemed him quite talented.

188
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:37,399
We greatly admired him,

189
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:38,679
and so bestowed the sword upon him.

190
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:39,799
But who would have thought

191
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:41,879
he would disappoint Us so.

192
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:43,960
Minister Yu,

193
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:45,120
does Our answer

194
00:10:45,519 --> 00:10:46,639
satisfy you?

195
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:47,799
I dare not.

196
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:48,840
I dare not.

197
00:10:49,279 --> 00:10:50,360
What the court does not know

198
00:10:51,399 --> 00:10:52,240
is that days ago,

199
00:10:52,679 --> 00:10:54,559
the strategies against the Tuoluo Kingdom,

200
00:10:55,039 --> 00:10:57,279
along with those brilliant verses,

201
00:10:57,759 --> 00:11:00,279
all came from Ning Chen's hand.

202
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:03,080
So it was him.

203
00:11:05,039 --> 00:11:06,440
So that's it.

204
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:09,320
So that's it. Now it makes sense.

205
00:11:10,039 --> 00:11:11,240
I should have realized.

206
00:11:11,799 --> 00:11:14,639
Why else would His Majesty so dote on him?

207
00:11:15,039 --> 00:11:17,159
I'm the real fool here.

208
00:11:17,360 --> 00:11:17,919
However,

209
00:11:18,759 --> 00:11:21,039
the entire court right now

210
00:11:21,159 --> 00:11:22,679
is demanding that We put you to death.

211
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:24,080
Ning Chen,

212
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:26,519
have you anything left to say?

213
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:37,840
This makes things easier.

214
00:11:39,759 --> 00:11:40,320
Your Majesty.

215
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:41,279
I...

216
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:45,960
I truly had no choice at the time.

217
00:11:46,320 --> 00:11:47,840
The Imperial Uncle, right before my eyes,

218
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:49,559
brutalized innocent civilians.

219
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:53,799
With the imperial sword in hand,

220
00:11:54,039 --> 00:11:55,320
and bearing Your Majesty's grace,

221
00:11:55,679 --> 00:11:57,559
how could I remain unmoved

222
00:11:57,960 --> 00:11:59,480
and stand idly by?

223
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:03,720
Besides, just consider this:

224
00:12:03,879 --> 00:12:05,159
the people of Zhenyuan County

225
00:12:05,519 --> 00:12:06,960
are all subjects of our Great Xuan.

226
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:10,679
If left with no way to live, what would they do?

227
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,759
They'd rebel!

228
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:15,720
Utter nonsense and scaremongering!

229
00:12:16,279 --> 00:12:17,639
In these prosperous times,

230
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:19,200
how could the people be suffering?

231
00:12:19,759 --> 00:12:21,759
I oversee the nation's lands,

232
00:12:22,039 --> 00:12:22,600
its fields,

233
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:23,399
its census,

234
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:24,320
its taxes,

235
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:27,080
salaries, and all related affairs.

236
00:12:27,399 --> 00:12:28,799
In recent years, the taxes

237
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:31,240
have always been paid first by Chongzhou.

238
00:12:31,679 --> 00:12:34,480
There's no way the people are suffering there.

239
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:36,600
You're clearly trying to escape blame,

240
00:12:36,960 --> 00:12:37,919
fabricating facts,

241
00:12:38,159 --> 00:12:39,159
exaggerating claims,

242
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:40,159
slandering the Imperial Uncle,

243
00:12:40,480 --> 00:12:41,600
and deceiving His Majesty!

244
00:12:43,120 --> 00:12:43,639
Old man,

245
00:12:44,279 --> 00:12:45,240
are you reciting a tongue twister?

246
00:12:45,879 --> 00:12:47,080
Have you ever been to Chongzhou?

247
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:49,519
Though I haven't been there,

248
00:12:49,919 --> 00:12:52,440
the annual taxes alone make it clear:

249
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:54,399
Chongzhou's people live and work in peace,

250
00:12:55,039 --> 00:12:56,039
happy and content.

251
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:56,879
That's bullshit!

252
00:12:57,639 --> 00:12:58,440
You think high taxes alone

253
00:12:58,600 --> 00:12:59,879
prove the people are doing well?

254
00:13:00,159 --> 00:13:01,120
What kind of twisted logic is that?

255
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:01,879
Did you come to court today

256
00:13:01,960 --> 00:13:03,399
and leave your brain at home?

257
00:13:03,679 --> 00:13:04,080
You...

258
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:04,679
You, you, you...

259
00:13:04,799 --> 00:13:06,000
Stop pointing that filthy finger at me!

260
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:07,559
Hearing is doubtful; seeing is believing.

261
00:13:07,679 --> 00:13:08,440
You've never even been to Chongzhou,

262
00:13:08,559 --> 00:13:08,960
so how can you claim

263
00:13:09,039 --> 00:13:10,440
the people there live in peace and joy?

264
00:13:10,720 --> 00:13:11,159
I...

265
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:11,960
I, I, I...

266
00:13:12,080 --> 00:13:13,080
Go get some sunshine in your spare time.

267
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:13,879
Get a bit of a tan,

268
00:13:14,080 --> 00:13:15,519
so no one calls you a pale idiot anymore.

269
00:13:15,639 --> 00:13:16,159
Pale idiot?

270
00:13:16,639 --> 00:13:17,360
You... I...

271
00:13:17,799 --> 00:13:18,399
I'm your grandpa!

272
00:13:18,559 --> 00:13:19,200
Can't even speak straight,

273
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:20,080
how did you even become an official?

274
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:21,960
And you dare pose as upright

275
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:23,039
and selfless?

276
00:13:23,159 --> 00:13:24,399
A corrupt dog like you in our Great Xuan

277
00:13:24,519 --> 00:13:26,399
is a sorrow to the people

278
00:13:26,559 --> 00:13:27,960
and a disgrace to the court!

279
00:13:28,159 --> 00:13:28,480
Let me tell you,

280
00:13:28,480 --> 00:13:29,799
people like you meet only one end:

281
00:13:29,960 --> 00:13:30,519
And that is,

282
00:13:30,799 --> 00:13:33,279
"Your name and body shall both be ruined,

283
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:36,360
while rivers flow on forever."

284
00:13:37,360 --> 00:13:38,000
That's you!

